ed several weeks before they hit the shelves*)<br><br><br>SPOTLIGHT ON IRON HAMMER GRAPHICS-<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> VECNA : HAND OF THE REVENANT VOLUME 1 GN (graphic novel)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> story by Modi Thorsson, art by Kevin MacCann</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br><br>From the birth of fantasy as a genre and for 30 years since, the name of Vecna has terrified generations of gamers and has been instrumental in creating the new sub-genre of fantasy-horror.  Now, three decades after his creation in the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Dungeons and Dragons</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> game, writer Modi Thorsson (<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Master of the Void, Lords of Creation</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->) and artist Kevin McCann (<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Battletech, Ravenloft</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->) bring the Whispered One into the world of graphic novels!  Thirty years of material, hundreds of submissions from fans, and two years of production time have finally brought to life the grim origins of one of the most sinister figures in all of Fantasy.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Vecna : Hand of the Revenant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is a dark journey into magic and horror both for the thousands who have grown up in Vecna's shadow, and those who have yet to feel that darkness!<br><br>(CAUT:4) MATURE READERS<br><br>SC, 7X10, 64pg, FC ...........................................$9.95<br><br>The cover art looks stunning.  It shows the Dark Revenant Vecna holding a glowing white orb which displays a scene on the battlefield.  Kas is on the battlefield riding in a chariot pulled by an undead horse raising his sword in the air.  In the background you can see that he is leading an army of undead, and to his side a necromancer turning one of the recently killed victims into a zombie...  <br><br>The art, as I said, is stunning and is enhanced subtlety with some computer special effects.  For example Vecna's left eye glows red, the orb glows white, skulls resting on pikes on the battlefield are also glowing with a white smoke, and the entire orb displaying the battle scene is subtlety transparent.   <br><br>I also like the tagline of the advertisement - <br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Sometimes the Heroes Lose... The secret history of one of Fantasy's most infamous villains makes happy endings a thing of the past...</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#97694F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub26.ezboard.com/uquintrel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quintrel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.lucasarts.com/products/outcast/images/downloads/icons/symbol.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Orcan Latrine Digger</span><br>  Posts: 303<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/7/02 2:25:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub26.ezboard.com/fapex71990frm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=325.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://216.40.197.199/webgraphics/clipart/animals/wolves/clipart_animals_wolves_001.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VECNA : HAND OF THE REVENANT </span><hr size=1> I am most glad to see you are back.<br><br><br>/dances jig <p><br><br><div align="right"><font size="5" face="Monotype Corsiva">Quintrel</div><font size="4"><div align="right"><a href="http://www.quintrel.150m.com">Mad Man Extrodinaire</a> </div></font></font><hr size="1" color=#b22222><center>"<i>Opportunity should be equal, must be equal, but achievement must remain individual.<i>"</center><font size="4" face="Monotype Corsiva"><div align="right">- Drizzt Do'Urden </div></font><hr size="1" color=#b22222></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub26.ezboard.com/fapex71990frm19.